newsitem.title: THAILAND: Thai baht up, interbank rate eases in late trade.
newsitem.headline: Thai baht up, interbank rate eases in late trade.

text.p: The baht was higher against the dollar in late trade on Wednesday in line with the weakening U.S. unit abroad, dealers said.
The better-than-expected economic data released today by finance ministry also helped boost the baht's sentiment against the dollar, dealers said.

The baht firmed to 25.842/25.852 to the dolar in late trade from 25.870/25.895 earlier and 25.885/25.895 late on Tuesday, dealers said. "The economic data were positive for the baht. There were some dollar selling for baht following the release of the figures," said one dealer at a European bank.
The one-month baht/dollar swap premium was traded at 12.30/13.30 satangs per dollar late compared with 13.50/14.50 earlier.
The Bank of Thailand fixed the mid-rate at 25.89 per dollar against 25.91 on Tuesday.
The overnight interbank rate was lower to 12.00-12.25 percent in late trade from 12.50 in the morning as the dollar buying helped increase the liquidity, dealers said.
